					<head>Karaite commentary</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597" rend="visible">
						<summary>An Arabic commentary on the book of Ecclesiastes.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="ara" otherLangs="he">Arabic and Hebrew</textLang>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85013597">
							<locus from="1r" to="129v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Commentary on Ecclesiastes </title>
							<note>Contains Exodus 13:17-15:1, 15:22-17:7, 18:1-21:36, 22:4-30:21, 30:33-32:29, 33:12-34:26. Pointed and accentuated Hebrew text, with a translation and short commentary in (Judeo-)Arabic.<p>The Hebrew text of Ecclesiastes, wirtten in Arabic characters, and provided with the Hebrew vowel-points, with an Arabic translation and commentary.</p>
								<p>Chapters: 1:1-2:21; 3:3-6; 16-17; 4:17; 5:7; 11:1-4; 12:3-14 are wanting.</p>
								<p>Text and translation are always introduced by a formula: قال قوهيلث and the comments by: قال الهغس.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
